results.name: Number of distinct groups of order n that are the torsion subgroup of an elliptic curve over the rationals Q.
comment: Barry Mazur proved that the torsion subgroup of an elliptic curve over Q is one of the 15 following groups: Z/NZ for N = 1, 2, …, 10, or 12, or Z/2Z × Z/2NZ with N = 1, 2, 3, 4.
reference: J. H. Silverman, The Arithmetic of Elliptic Curves, Graduates Texts in Mathematics 106, Springer-Verlag, 1986 (see Theorem 7.5).
link: B. Mazur, Rational isogenies of prime degree, Inventiones Math. 44, 2 (June 1978), 129-162.
example: a(4) = 2 because a subgroup of order 4 in an elliptic curve over Q is isomorphic to one of the 2 groups Z/4Z or Z/2Z × Z/2Z.
xref: Cf. A059765 (possible sizes of the torsion subgroup of an elliptic curve over Q), A146879.
results.author: _Jonathan Sondow_, Jan 12 2013
